    <string name="terms_of_service_body">Terms of Service\n\nLast updated: July 16, 2026\n\nWelcome to Calories. By using this application, you agree to the following terms.\n\n1. Purpose of the App\nCalories is a personal nutrition and fitness tracking tool. It helps you log meals, monitor macros, track weight, and set daily calorie goals. Information shown in the app is for general wellness purposes only and is not medical advice.\n\n2. Your Account\nYou are responsible for keeping your login credentials secure and for activity that occurs under your account. Provide accurate profile information so calorie estimates remain useful.\n\n3. Health Disclaimer\nCalorie targets, BMI values, and activity estimates are approximations. Always consult a qualified healthcare professional before making significant changes to your diet or exercise routine, especially if you have a medical condition.\n\n4. User Content\nFood logs, weight entries, and other data you enter belong to you. You grant us permission to store and process that data solely to provide app features such as syncing, reminders, and progress charts.\n\n5. Privacy\nWe handle personal data in line with our privacy practices. Local data on your device can be cleared from Profile → Delete Your Data. Remote account data may remain until you request account deletion through supported channels.\n\n6. Acceptable Use\nDo not misuse the service, attempt unauthorized access, reverse engineer protected components, or use the app in any way that violates applicable law.\n\n7. Availability\nFeatures may change, and temporary outages can occur. We strive for reliability but do not guarantee uninterrupted service.\n\n8. Limitation of Liability\nTo the fullest extent permitted by law, Calories and its developers are not liable for indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from use of the app or reliance on its estimates.\n\n9. Changes to These Terms\nWe may update these Terms of Service from time to time. Continued use of the app after changes means you accept the revised terms.\n\n10. Contact\nIf you have questions about these terms, contact support through the channels listed in the app store listing or project documentation.\n\nThank you for using Calories responsibly.</string>
